article.headline: Nicholls State 73, SE Louisiana 66
article.story: THIBODAUX, La. (AP) -- Adonis Gray scored 20 points to help Nicholls State take a 73-66 victory over Southeastern Louisiana on Saturday night. Stefan Blaszczynski added 12 points for Nicholls (7-8, 3-1 Southland Conference), which rallied from a 33-25 halftime deficit by shooting nearly 63 percent (15-for-24) from the field in the second half, including 6-of-8 from 3-point range. Ricky Woods had 20 points and 11 rebounds to lead Southeastern (8-7, 2-2), while Chris Lee scored 15 points and Terry Bryant 14. Nicholls went 15-of-18 from the free throw line in defeating Southeastern for the first time since February of 2002. The Lions were 7-of-16 from the foul line. Michael Czepil's 3-pointer gave the Colonels the lead for good, 53-52, with 6:56 remaining. Southeastern closed to 67-65 on Micheal Cyprien's putback with 1:07 left, but the Colonels closed out the game with six free throws, including four by Gray, who finished 6-for-7 from the foul line. <
